data.description: FULLY RENOVATED 3BR/1BA home has been tastefully updated with beautiful floors, windows, kitchen, and bath. Enter through the front door into the main living area where you will immediately appreciate the gorgeous ceramic tile flooring that flows seamlessly throughout the main living areas.  All three bedrooms are furnished with laminate flooring, nice-sized closets, and ceiling fans with lights.  Thoughtful design attributes during the bathroom renovation include a large sink, updated fixtures, and attractive shower tile that extends outside the shower adding personality to the walls. The modern kitchen is well-equipped with shaker-style cabinets, granite countertops, tile backsplash, pantry, and an eating area offering views out through the glass sliders to the patio and back yard. Step out to enjoy the back yard with a patio area perfect for barbeques, hot tub, sun tanning, eating alfresco, or simply relaxing and enjoying the Florida weather.  Kids and pets have plenty of space to play in a nice-sized, fully fenced-in back yard with a shed to store toys, tools, and a lawn mower. The patio spa does not convey. Newer, Roof (2017) with leased solar panels providing the benefit of low monthly electric bills. The solar panels’ lease must be transferred to the new owner. Located just west of US HWY 19 for easy commute and convenient to shopping centers, restaurants, and award-winning beaches and parks. Less than 5 miles from Tarpon Springs Sponge Docks, Less than 7 miles to Innisbrook/Copperhead golf course in Palm Harbor. Award winning beaches include  Fred Howard Park and Beach just 8 miles away and 15 miles to the Dunedin Causeway/Honeymoon Island State Park and Beach.  Don’t miss this great opportunity. Schedule your private showing today!
